{
  "text": "Several inhibitors of AURKA/B including Hesperadin (B>A), MLN8237 (A>B), ZM447439 (B>A), VX680 (A=B) and AZD1152 (B>>>A) have been developed as anti-cancer agents with encouraging anti-tumoral potential in vitro and in vivo [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . However, the underlying tumor-specific mechanisms of the anti-neoplastic activities of these drugs are still poorly understood.",
  "correct_citation": {
